description:
English digital chapters for the Metabarons Genesis: Castaka graphic novel.

Before the Metabarons there were the Castakas, a clan of lawless pirates - this is their story. The Metabarons recounted the extraordinary saga of the genealogy of the galaxy's ultimate warrior. But his ancestors also had ancestors. And far from being noble warriors with an inflexible code, one will discover they were in fact disloyal, vengeful pirates born out of brutality and war. From legendary creator Alexandro Jodorowsky and artist Das Pastoras, and for all of those who dreamt of a sequel to The Metabarons, comes instead the origin tale of their first ancestor, Dayal de Castaka.
name: Metabarons Genesis: Castaka

description:
Reprints of "Il Tromba" series, with previously unreleased covers by Gianni Pinaglia.

The 1st series, published by Edifumetto, has 81 issues.

The 2nd series, published by Edittrice Squalo (Edifumetto with a different name) has 4 issues.

The first series has 2 reprints each issue, in chronological order. Starting from #39, the volume reprints one issue of "Il Tromba" series and one issue of "Batty & Gay" series. From #51, the volume reprints one issue of "Il Tromba" series and one issue of various stories, many of them coming from "Fumetti Folk" series. From #64, the volume reprints one issue of "Il Tromba" series, one issue of "Il camionista" series and one issue of "Gol" series, the second series continuing the reprints of these 3 volumes.
name: Super Tromba
